'''细根'''（{{lang-en|'''fine root'''}}），是指[[植物根系|植物根系]]中周转较快的那部分根，作为媒介传输土壤中的营养元素及水分至植物中<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=http://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-642-22067-8_18|title=Measuring Roots|last=Lukac|first=Martin|date=2012-01-01|publisher=Springer Berlin Heidelberg|isbn=9783642220661|editor-last=Mancuso|editor-first=Stefano|pages=363–373|language=en|chapter=Fine Root Turnover|doi=10.1007/978-3-642-22067-8_18}}</ref>。细根周转（turnover）的过程中会释放大量的[[碳|碳]]进入土壤中，形成大量的土壤有机质。土壤有机质受到环境的影响（气温、水分、肥料）会迅速释放大量的CO<sub>2</sub>，从而受到了广泛学者的关注。

北方森林（boreal forest）只占陆地土壤面积的15% 却拥有约33%的净初级生产力（NPP），对环境的变化最为敏感<ref>{{Cite book|url=http://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-94-009-6833-2_9|title=Tree Root Systems and Their Mycorrhizas|last=Persson|first=Hans Å|date=1983-01-01|publisher=Springer Netherlands|isbn=9789400968356|editor-last=Atkinson|editor-first=D.|series=Developments in Plant and Soil Sciences|pages=87–101|language=en|chapter=The distribution and productivity of fine roots in boreal forests|doi=10.1007/978-94-009-6833-2_9#page-1}}</ref>。细根通常< 2mm，寿命远远小于粗根，从几个月到几年不等。为了准确估计细根寿命，目前研究通常用直径 < 1mm的细根<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Heljae_Sisko_Helmisaari/publication/6169067_Fine_root_biomass_in_relation_to_site_and_stand_characteristics_in_Norway_spruce_and_Scots_pine_stands/links/5570651708aeffcab353bd6a/Fine-root-biomass-in-relation-to-site-and-stand-characteristics-in-Norway-spruce-and-Scots-pine-stands.pdf|title=Fine root biomass in relation to site and stand characteristics in Norway spruce and Scots pine stands|accessdate=2017-03-22|author=|date=|work=web.b.ebscohost.com|publisher=|language=en}}</ref>。

研究方法主要有土钻法、内生长法／纱网法、微根管法（Minirhizotron）和同位素法，目前最准确的方法是微根管法，但每种方法仍有各自的利弊<ref name=":0" />。研究表明根系寿命和根系直径、土壤深度呈正相关，与土壤温度、肥性及含水量呈负相关<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Fine root turnover and litter production of Norway spruce in a long-term temperature and nutrient manipulation experiment|url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11104-013-1853-3|last=Leppälammi-Kujansuu|first=Jaana|last2=Salemaa|first2=Maija|date=2014-01-01|journal=Plant and Soil|issue=1-2|doi=10.1007/s11104-013-1853-3|volume=374|pages=73–88|language=en|issn=0032-079X|last3=Kleja|first3=Dan Berggren|last4=Linder|first4=Sune|last5=Helmisaari|first5=Heljä-Sisko}}</ref>。不同树种的根系寿命也不同，通常落叶性树种与针叶树种相比具有更短的根系寿命<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Fine root production and turnover of tree and understorey vegetation in Scots pine, silver birch and Norway spruce stands in SW Sweden|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0378112713000662|last=Hansson|first=Karna|last2=Helmisaari|first2=Heljä-Sisko|date=2013-12-01|journal=Forest Ecology and Management|doi=10.1016/j.foreco.2013.01.022|series=Influence of tree species on forest soils: New evidence from field studies|volume=309|pages=58–65|last3=Sah|first3=Shambhu P.|last4=Lange|first4=Holger}}</ref>。

